<title>USA: Farah stake cut by Marciano group to 4 pct.</title>
<headline>Farah stake cut by Marciano group to 4 pct.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-04-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Georges Marciano, former chairman of Yes Clothing Co, said Friday he reduced his stake in Farah Inc to four percent or 405,900 shares.</p>
<p>In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Marciano's group said it sold 150,000 shares of the El Paso, Texas, maker of men's slacks between April 2 and April 15 at $10 to $11 each.</p>
